{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011DqWjeQvFbjjKr3bKr3Dhp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture of the spark-pi namespace. Let me analyze what I see:\n\n**Current State:**\n\n1. **Image versions**: Both deployments (spark-master, spark-worker) and the job (spark-pi) use `apache/spark:3.5.3`. This is a non-default version (latest as of this writing is 3.5.4 or possibly 4.x).\n\n2. **Resource limits (non-default)**:\n   - spark-master: cpu limit=500m, memory limit=1Gi; requests cpu=200m, memory=512Mi\n   - spark-worker: cpu limit=500m, memory limit=1Gi; requests cpu=200m, memory=512Mi\n   - spark-pi job: cpu limit=500m, memory limit=1Gi; requests cpu=200m, memory=512Mi\n\n3. **Job parameters (non-default)**:\n   - SparkPi job uses `--master local[2]` (running locally, not connecting to the spark-master)\n   - `--driver-memory 512m`\n   - Pi approximation iterations: **1000** (default is typically 2)\n   - `backoffLimit: 0` (no retries on failure)\n\n4. **RBAC setup**: The spark-pi ServiceAccount has a role granting permissions on services, configmaps, and persistent volume claims, but notably lacks access to pods and events resources, which could be problematic if Spark needs to manage those.\n\n5. **Worker setup**: The spark-worker is configured with 1GB memory and 1 core, running a single replica.\n\n6. **Architecture mismatch**: There's a fundamental inconsistency here—the cluster deploys a spark-master and spark-worker, but the job bypasses them entirely by running locally with `--master local[2]`, so it's not actually using the cluster infrastructure.\n\nFor an upgrade plan, I should think about what needs to change. The image version could be bumped from 3.5.3 to a newer stable release, though I'd need to check for breaking changes. The resource constraints are concerning—the worker's 1GB memory limit matches its allocation exactly, which leaves no headroom and risks OOM errors in production. The job parameters also need attention: switching from local mode to connecting to the actual spark-master cluster would make better use of the infrastructure, and increasing the backoffLimit from 0 would improve resilience for production workloads.\n\nOn the RBAC side, the current role grants delete and patch permissions on persistent volume claims but is missing pods—which the Spark driver needs to create executor pods if we move to cluster mode. The worker count is also just one replica, which could be scaled up for real workloads. The core issue is that the job configuration doesn't align with the cluster setup: it's running in local mode when it should be pointing to the spark-master service and using either cluster or client mode for distributed execution.\n\nNow I'll put together the migration plan and create the necessary ConfigMap.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1193,"cache_read_input_tokens":32300,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1193},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8ff25c8-9288-49f5-a32c-acd0c3cb3086","uuid":"dc95ce19-1b86-472c-a52e-9358c9c0257e","request_id":"req_011CcMWwde4YQP7svqe73fiH"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011DqWjeQvFbjjKr3bKr3Dhp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have a complete picture of the namespace. Now I'll write the plan and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1193,"cache_read_input_tokens":32300,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1193},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8ff25c8-9288-49f5-a32c-acd0c3cb3086","uuid":"87227e92-ec20-44e7-a1ec-96934c7bd734","request_id":"req_011CcMWwde4YQP7svqe73fiH"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011DqWjeQvFbjjKr3bKr3Dhp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01G6dw5gsKoGXDZJfpbARZLY","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLAN'\n# Spark-Pi Namespace — Maintenance Upgrade Plan\nDate: 2026-06-24\nPrepared by: Operations Team (automated inspection)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current-State Summary\n\n| Resource | Key settings |\n|---|---|\n| spark-master Deployment | image: apache/spark:3.5.3, cpu 200m–500m, mem 512Mi–1Gi, replicas: 1 |\n| spark-worker Deployment | image: apache/spark:3.5.3, cpu 200m–500m, mem 512Mi–1Gi, replicas: 1, SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1 |\n| spark-pi Job | image: apache/spark:3.5.3, --master local[2], --driver-memory 512m, pi-iterations 1000, backoffLimit: 0 |\n| ServiceAccount | spark-pi (dedicated, non-default) |\n| Role spark-pi-role | verbs: create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims |\n| RoleBinding | spark-pi-role-binding → spark-pi SA |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues and Planned Changes\n\n### 2.1 Image Version Upgrade (apache/spark:3.5.3 → 3.5.4 or later)\n\n**Risk:** Medium — minor version bumps in Spark 3.5.x series have historically been\nbackward-compatible, but must verify JVM and Python compatibility.\n\n**Change:**\n- Update `spec.template.spec.containers[0].image` in spark-master, spark-worker Deployments\n  and the spark-pi Job template to the target version tag.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master -n spark-pi\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\nkubectl logs -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master | grep -i \"starting\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 Resource Limits — Worker Memory Headroom\n\n**Issue:** spark-worker has `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G` (JVM heap) with a container\nmemory limit of `1Gi`. The JVM overhead (off-heap, native memory) will push total\nresident memory above 1Gi, risking OOMKill.\n\n**Change:**\n- Increase spark-worker memory limit to `1536Mi` (or `2Gi` for production headroom)\n  while keeping the request at `512Mi`.\n- Optionally raise `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY` to `1200m` if limit is raised to `1536Mi`.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl top pod -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker\n# Confirm no OOMKilled events:\nkubectl describe pod -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker | grep -i oom\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 Resource Limits — Master CPU\n\n**Issue:** spark-master is capped at `500m` CPU. Under heavy scheduling load\n(many concurrent jobs) this can throttle the master and delay task assignment.\n\n**Change:**\n- Increase spark-master cpu limit to `1000m` (1 core).\n- Adjust request to `300m`.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl top pod -n spark-pi -l app=spark-master\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 Job Execution Mode — Local vs Cluster\n\n**Issue:** The spark-pi Job submits with `--master local[2]`, which runs entirely\ninside the driver container and ignores the spark-master and spark-worker Deployments.\nThis defeats the purpose of maintaining the cluster Deployments.\n\n**Change (choose one approach, confirm with team before execution):**\n\nOption A — Use the running Spark standalone cluster:\n```\n--master spark://spark-master:7077\n```\nRemove `--master local[2]` and `--driver-memory 512m`; driver runs as a client\nconnecting to the master service.\n\nOption B — Keep local mode, decommission master/worker Deployments:\nRemove the spark-master and spark-worker Deployments if standalone cluster is not needed.\n\n**Recommended:** Option A, to leverage the cluster already deployed.\n\n**Verification (Option A):**\n```\nkubectl logs -n spark-pi -l app=spark-pi,component=driver --tail=50\n# Look for: \"Pi is roughly\" and connection to spark://spark-master:7077\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 Job Resilience — backoffLimit\n\n**Issue:** `backoffLimit: 0` means a single transient failure (e.g., node pressure,\nimage pull delay) permanently fails the Job with no retry.\n\n**Change:**\n- Set `backoffLimit: 2` to tolerate transient failures while still surfacing\n  real application errors after 3 attempts total.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl describe job spark-pi -n spark-pi | grep -i backoff\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.6 RBAC — Missing 'pods' Verb for Cluster Mode\n\n**Issue:** If the Job is switched to cluster mode (Change 2.4, Option A), the Spark\ndriver will attempt to create executor Pods. The current Role grants no permissions\non the `pods` resource, causing a 403 error.\n\n**Change:**\n- Add a new rule to spark-pi-role:\n```yaml\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"pods\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# Expected: yes\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.7 RBAC — Restrict PVC Delete Permission\n\n**Issue:** spark-pi-role grants `delete` on `persistentvolumeclaims`. Unless the\nSpark job actively creates and owns PVCs, this is an over-privileged permission.\n\n**Change:**\n- Remove `delete` from the PVC verbs, leaving: `create`, `get`, `list`, `watch`,\n  `update`, `patch`.\n- If PVC cleanup is required, scope it to a dedicated maintenance Role.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl auth can-i delete persistentvolumeclaims \\\n  --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# Expected: no\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.8 Worker Replica Count\n\n**Issue:** Single spark-worker replica (`replicas: 1`) provides no parallelism for\nthe Spark standalone cluster.\n\n**Change:**\n- Scale spark-worker to `replicas: 2` (or more) to enable actual distributed execution.\n- Adjust `SPARK_WORKER_CORES` to match available node capacity (currently `1`).\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker\n# Confirm 2+ pods in Running state\nkubectl logs -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master | grep -i \"registered worker\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Execution Order\n\nApply changes in this order to minimize disruption:\n\n1. **RBAC first** (2.6, 2.7) — no restart required; takes effect immediately.\n2. **Image upgrade** (2.1) — rolling update; master first, then worker.\n3. **Resource limits** (2.2, 2.3) — triggers rolling restarts; apply after image is verified.\n4. **Worker scale-out** (2.8) — after limits are confirmed stable.\n5. **Job changes** (2.4, 2.5) — update Job spec last; requires deleting and re-creating\n   the completed/failed Job object (Jobs are immutable once created).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Plan\n\n- Deployments: `kubectl rollout undo deploy/<name> -n spark-pi`\n- RBAC: re-apply the original Role YAML from version control.\n- Job: re-apply the original Job YAML (with `local[2]` and `backoffLimit: 0`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Pre-Change Checklist\n\n- [ ] Confirm target Spark image tag exists in registry and is scanned (no critical CVEs).\n- [ ] Validate cluster has sufficient node capacity for 2 workers + master + driver.\n- [ ] Agree on execution mode (Option A vs B for Change 2.4) with application owner.\n- [ ] Schedule change window during low-traffic period.\n- [ ] Ensure `kubectl rollout` permissions are available for the operator account.\nPLAN\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap with migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1193,"cache_read_input_tokens":32300,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1193},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8ff25c8-9288-49f5-a32c-acd0c3cb3086","uuid":"bb79310b-cac3-49ca-9839-bd3788f0a1e6","request_id":"req_011CcMWwde4YQP7svqe73fiH"}
